(17, 1, '2013-01-27 03:59:08', '2013-01-27 03:59:08', 'Abusers can use relatively inexpensive software to spy on your phone, giving them access to your text messages, call history and even GPS location. Some spy software goes so far as to turn your camera on in "stealth mode," recording your movements and conversations. If your abuser knows where you are, who you''re talking to and what you''re talking about, he could have installed this software on your phone.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nThe first test you can run, if safe to do so, is leaving your phone at home and going somewhere you wouldn''t normally go. See if your abuser asks you why you went there or how it was. You can also try taking your phone with you somewhere outside your home and saying something out loud while no one else is there.\r\n\r\nIf you believe your phone or mobile device is what he''s using to track you, here are some steps you can take to stop him:\r\n<h1 dir="ltr" id="internal-source-marker_0.5687615667920306">Tools for De-Stalkifying Your Phone:</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">If you have an Android, you can run an app that will try to find spyware. There may be kinds of spyware it doesn’t recognize, but if it does find spyware, it will let you uninstall it.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><a title="Android spyware detector" href=" https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.soundmobilesystems.android.spyappdetector&amp;hl=en" target="_blank">Android spyware detector</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">If you have an iPhone, or if you did not detect spyware on your Android but are still suspicious it’s being tracked, you can reset your phone to make sure it is clean. However, this will erase all of the other data and apps you have stored on your phone as well.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir="ltr">-- Android: Do a factory reset. To get to the factory reset option, go to the menu and select the settings button. Then select the “Privacy” option. Factory data reset will be the last option under “Privacy.” Click that, and then press the “Reset Phone” button.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_embedded&amp;v=y4Bi8QI5KyA">Video tutorial on resetting your Android</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href="http://www.fuerza.is/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Android-factory-reset.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-40 aligncenter" alt="Android factory reset" src="http://www.fuerza.is/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Android-factory-reset-180x300.png" width="180" height="300" /></a>\r\n<p dir="ltr">-- iPhone: Restore your original settings. Do this by syncing your iPhone using iTunes. Go to the page you would normally use in iTunes as a home page to update your music or apps. On the home screen, underneath the “Check for Update” button, you will see the “Restore” button.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><a href="http://www.fuerza.is/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/iPhone-reset-screenshot.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-41 aligncenter" alt="iPhone reset screenshot" src="http://www.fuerza.is/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/iPhone-reset-screenshot-300x50.png" width="335" height="55" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"></p>', 'Check Your Device', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'check-your-phone', '', '', '2013-01-27 16:28:27', '2013-01-27 16:28:27', '', 0, 'http://www.fuerza.is/?page_id=17', 0, 'page', '', 0),
