(54, 3, '2013-01-27 17:17:40', '2013-01-27 17:17:40', 'Abusers can buy software that track every keystroke you make on your computer, giving them access to your emails, Internet history and passwords. They can also relatively easily check your browser history to see which sites you''ve been visiting. <!--more--><em></em>\r\n\r\n<em>Detecting and Thwarting Keystroke Loggers</em>\r\n\r\nFinding and Stopping a Keystroke Logger on a PC:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Press the "Ctrl," "Shift" and "Esc" keys at the same time to start the Task Manager.</li>\r\n	<li>Click the "Processes" tab in the Task Manager''s window.</li>\r\n	<li>Select "winnetcl.exe" from the list of the processes and click "End Process" button.</li>\r\n	<li>Select "webebot.exe" from the list of the processes and click "End Process" button.</li>\r\n	<li>Close the Task Manager.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWorking Around a Keystroke Logger on a PC:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Click on Start</li>\r\n	<li>Go to All Programs</li>\r\n	<li>Click onAccessories</li>\r\n	<li>Select Accessibility</li>\r\n	<li>Click on On-Screen Keyboard</li>\r\n	<li>Use the on-screen keyboard to type using your mouse instead of your physical keyboard.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWorking around a Keystroke Logger on a Mac\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Click on the tiny flag on the menu bar at the upper right of your screen.</li>\r\n	<li>Click "show keyboard viewer."</li>\r\n	<li>Click the letters on the screen instead of typing on your keyboard.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href="http://www.fuerza.is/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Onscreen-keyboard.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-52 aligncenter" alt="Onscreen keyboard" src="http://www.fuerza.is/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Onscreen-keyboard-300x136.png" width="300" height="136" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em>Clearing Your Browser History</em>\r\n\r\nIf your abuser knows what Internet websites you are visiting, but you don’t believe he’s logging keystrokes, or if you have already removed the keystroke logging device, you should regularly delete your browser history.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Firefox:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li dir="ltr">In the bar at the top of your screen or browser, select “Tools.” There should be an option called “Clear Recent History.” Click on that.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<a href="http://www.fuerza.is/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Firefox-tools-browser.png"><img class="aligncenter" alt="Firefox tools browser" src="http://www.fuerza.is/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Firefox-tools-browser-300x162.png" width="300" height="162" /></a>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li dir="ltr">If you have an older version of Firefox, go to the “Tools” menu and click “Options.” On the menu that pops up, click the “Privacy” button, go to “History,” and click “Clear.”</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<a href="http://www.fuerza.is/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Firefox-clear-history.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-47 aligncenter" alt="Firefox clear history" src="http://www.fuerza.is/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Firefox-clear-history-300x263.png" width="300" height="263" /></a>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Safari\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li dir="ltr">Go to the History option on the menu. The last option on the menu will be “Clear History.” Click it.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href="http://www.fuerza.is/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Safari-delete-history.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-48 aligncenter" alt="Safari delete history" src="http://www.fuerza.is/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Safari-delete-history-300x144.png" width="300" height="144" /></a>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Chrome:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol start="2">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li dir="ltr">Go to History on the browser menu. The last item on the drop-down menu will be “Show all history.” Click it.</li>\r\n	<li dir="ltr">A list of your browser history will pop up in a new window. A button at the top will say “Clear all browsing data.” Click that.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<a href="http://www.fuerza.is/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Chrome-screenshot-1.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-50 aligncenter" alt="Chrome screenshot 1" src="http://www.fuerza.is/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Chrome-screenshot-1-300x151.png" width="300" height="151" /></a>\r\n<ol start="2">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li dir="ltr">The pop-up menu will give you a drop down-menu for how much data you want to erase, and a series of options to click. Click all of the options, and from the drop-down menu pick “the beginning of time.”</li>\r\n	<li dir="ltr">Click “Clear browsing data.”</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<a href="http://www.fuerza.is/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Chrome-screenshot-2.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-49 aligncenter" alt="Chrome screenshot 2" src="http://www.fuerza.is/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Chrome-screenshot-2-300x207.png" width="300" height="207" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Check Your Computer', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '19-revision-5', '', '', '2013-01-27 17:17:40', '2013-01-27 17:17:40', '', 19, 'http://www.fuerza.is/19-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
